    <solution><p>Trying to calculate <m>3^{400}</m> or <m>4^{300}</m> results in very large numbers. Notice that <m>3^{400}=3^{(4\cdot 100)}\text{.}</m> Also, notice that <m>4^{300}=4^{(3\cdot100)}\text{.}</m> So to know if <m>3^{400}</m> or <m>4^{300}</m> is bigger, we only have to compare <m>3^{4}</m> with <m>4^{3}\text{.}</m></p>
</solution>
